cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SE

The paper discusses the concept of penetration testing and security audit, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach for conducting comprehensive what-if analyses involves the use of simulated penetration testing, which requires the application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The analysis is performed on a network model, which is a subfield of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the prioritization of counter-measures subject to a given budget, which is related to the field of software engineering (cs.SE) and system integration (cs.SI).
